social_posts.post_text: Being back and bouldering in Hueco Tanks with friends @jasonkehl_cryptochild and @martinamali was such a nice break from digging and all the necessary work involved with preparing my property for future climbing camps and a location for kids training camps in the near future!
I'm excited to announce that my climbing technique video called, The Fundmentals of Climbing is now available. Go to my website to find the link.

My dear friend, Maria Cranor passed away on Sunday. Maria was there the very first day I went climbing in Big Rock, CA. Her big smile and bubbling enthusiasm was so welcoming and supportive. Maria was very much loved by all her friends and colleagues and I'm very grateful for her friendship and positive impact on my life 🙏
Happy Friday! Anyone interested in watching the introduction to my Fundamentals of Climbing video can watch it on my YouTube channel. Enjoy!

It was a pleasure to hang out with Babsi Zangeri, her partner Jacapo Larcher, who each did an impressive on-sight ascent of the famous Eternal Flame (5.13a) route in Pakistan. Respect! Also hanging out after the Reel Rock 17 film showing was Seb Bouin, one of the strongest and most humble climbers of this generation. "Resistance Climbing" starring Andrew Bisharat, was also a great film that shows an adorable group of climbers who  find solace and freedom in the conflict-torn area of Palestine.

It's almost time for the Lynn Hill Climbing Camp in Joshua Tree: April 28th-30th. There are only 10 spots available so sign up today with Cliffhanger Guides for a fun learning experience with cool people in a magical place!
It was such good medicine for the soul to see Ani DiFranco at the Boulder Theater tonight. I'm so grateful to hear the sweet music of such an inspiring musician!
Sasha and I are almost done placing bolts on our new route in the Flatirons! We're both excited to try free climbing it soon!

It was great to see everyone at the BCC (Boulder Climbing. Community) event at Neptune Mountaineering!With the rapidly growing climbing community here on the Front Range and beyond, we certainly need more trail work and re-bolting efforts to keep climbing safe and sustainable for future generations of climbers! Thanks to everyone who have shown up as volunteers and for all your contributions to this worthwhile non-profit organization!

Today is the 3rd annual on-line fundraiser for the @yosemiteclimbingassociation. There will also be a party in South Lake Tahoe on June 2nd where the legendary Peter Croft will be a guest speaker. Sign up and join the fun!

It was fun to get back up on a multi-pitch route again with @ninacaprez in Presles located in the Vercors region of France. Thankfully I wore the perfect shirt made of a merino wool fabric blended with a high tech fiber called 37.5. The 37.5 technology helps maintain the ideal body temperature whether I'm generating heat while climbing or when cooling down at the belay.

The Go Pro Mountain Games were fun to be a part of this year. There is so much talent out there from the bouldering competition, to the slack lining acrobatics, and all of the other river rafting and running and mountain biking activities going on each day. Fortunately it only rained a bit and it was great to see so many families and friends having fun in the sun!

I'm so grateful for the chance to return to Italy to share stories at a film festival in Valloriate called Nuovi Mondi and to climb and hang out with my friends in Finale Ligure. Though summer is not the ideal season, I look forward to returning in the winter and staying at my friend's B&B called, Il Bandito e la Principessa.
The people, food, weather and the endless limestone cliffs in the area make this area one of the best winter destinations I know of!
Please donate whatever you can afford to help the community in Maui after such a devastating fire🙏 Global Climbing Community GoFundme.com

It was a great trip to the Climbing Festival in the Czech Republic in Teplice Metují- the place where climbing in bold style began 100 years ago! I climbed one of these classic routes placing only knots in constrictions in the cracks between the ring bolts that are used as belay points on these fairy tale like formations! 
It's always very special to have a chance to hang out with some old friends that shared some of these fun times together!

I'm so happy to have discovered this live local music venue a few blocks from my house at the Stone Cottage Studios. Last night featured Christopher Morse and the Pamela Machala band. I was very impressed by the quality of the music and by neighbors who started this music venue!

I'm so happy to have discovered this music venue a few blocks from my house at the Stone Cottage Studios! I was impressed by the quality of the music and by my neighbors who started this live music venue with local musicians. Christopher Morse did a great job opening the show for the all female Pamela Machala band playing in this video.
This unexpected gathering at the boulders in Little Cottonwood canyon with a few old friends and new friends from Orlando, Florida was a super fun and memorable day!
Congratulations on writing this book AND getting married this month Sasha!

I'm so happy to have finally sent the last pitch of the new "Queenline" route on the south face of the Maiden that Sasha DiGiulian and I bolted last winter! Sasha sent all three pitches ground up on Tuesday (tentatively rated 5.11+, 5.13c, 5.13d) after a 4 month break due a knee injury. I waited to return to this route with Sasha until after she had recovered from this injury, got married, and then went on a book tour to promote her new book, "Take the Lead". I hope to send all three pitches ground up once the weather is a bit cooler!

After a few attempts to free the entire route in a day, I finally succeeded on the new route @sashadigiulian and I bolted on the south face of the Maiden. It was extra challenging with very warm and sunny conditions, but the weather should be perfect as cooler temperatures arrive! Thanks for the belay and photo by Kevin Capps!
Mañana vengo a Espagña! Ven al festival Amunt El 18 Noviembre para ver la mia presentación!
null

I'm grateful for another amazing trip to Barcelona as a guest speaker at the Amunt Festival. Thanks to the hospitality of Jose Lloret and family in Barcelona. Also, thanks to my girl friends from over 30 years ago back in the early days of competition: Anna Ibanez, Montse Pascual, and Mariona Marti Sans - thanks for taking me to climb in Montgrony for the first time! Also thanks to Chris Sharma for taking me to Margalef for the first time! Thank you all for the good times and fun climbing at these classic limestone crags!

The Written in Stone podcast by Kris Hampton is a well researched and amusing recounting of rock climbing history, starting in the 90's.
It's well worth listening to it!

I finally got Covid for the first time after my 4th trip to Europe this year. At least I found a productive way to quarantine while tiling my new bath/shower building in Hueco Tanks, TX. Thanks to Glenn Johnson and Dan for all their help building the structure. I look forward to able to offer some fun climbing camps out there soon!

Still sending. Still parenting. Still evolving.
